tern England): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Gruffudd</i>, Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, composed of the elements <i>grip</i>, of uncertain significance, + <i>iud</i> ‘chief, lord’."],"variants":[{"name":"Griffieth","meanings":["Variant of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griff","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone living near a pit or hollow, from Middle English <i>grif</i> ‘pit, hollow, narrow valley’ (Old Norse <i>gryfja</i>), or a habitational name from Griff in Warwickshire, Griffe in Derbyshire, or Griff Farm in Rievaulx, North Yorkshire, all probably named with this word.","Welsh and English: from the Welsh personal name <i>Gryff</i>, a short form of <i>Gruffudd</i>. See   Griffith  .","German: variant of   Greif   1."]},{"name":"Kerfoot","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Cheshire):","habitational name, probably from Carefoot, near Myerscough (Lancashire).","possibly a variant of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffes","meanings":["Welsh: altered form of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffeth","meanings":["Altered form of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffiths","meanings":["Welsh (Glamorgan and western England): Anglicized form of the patronymic <i>(ap) Gruffudd</i>, from Old Welsh <i>Grippiud</i> (see   Griffith  )."]},{"name":"Griffth","meanings":["Variant of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffitt","meanings":["Altered form of   Griffith  ."]}]},{"name":"Howel","type":"FIRST","meanings":["The English form of the Welsh name Hywel."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Howel ap Griffith was born about 1317, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Griffith ap Rhys, was 42 and his mother, Mrs Griffith ap Rhys, was 33. He had at least 1 son with Mrs Howel ap Griffith."},"et":{"abt 1317–":"umbes 1317–Surnud","1317–Male":"1317–Surnud","1319–Female":"1319–Surnud","1328–Female":"1328–Surnud","1357–Male":"1357–Surnud","1276–Male":"1276–Surnud","1286–Female":"1286–Surnud","1357":"1357","abt 1317":"umbes 1317","abt. 1357":"umbes 1357","1276":"1276","1286":"1286